Currently, Portfolio does not consider Remaining Time as a factor in Sprint planning. For instance, if an Epic or Story has been assigned to Sprint A, and Sprint A has 5 days left but the remaining estimate of the work is still 10 days, Portfolio will keep those Epics/Stories in Sprint A instead of planning ahead by starting to push the work into the next sprint. It might be a good idea to allow for the option to have remaining time be taken into account in planning, as it could give users a more accurate glance into future planning if a sprint is starting to become overbooked with items that have taken longer than originally estimated.

